#: ../../skills.rst:2
msgid "研究技能"
msgstr "Research Skills"

#: ../../skills.rst:4
msgid "AgentSociety 2 包含一组 LLM 原生的研究技能，用于自动化科学研究工作流。"
msgstr ""
"AgentSociety 2 includes a set of LLM-native research skills for automating "
"scientific research workflows."

#: ../../skills.rst:7
msgid "概述"
msgstr "Overview"

#: ../../skills.rst:9
msgid "研究技能模块提供以下功能："
msgstr "The research skills module provides the following capabilities:"

#: ../../skills.rst:11
msgid "**文献检索**: 搜索和管理学术论文"
msgstr "**Literature Search**: Search and manage academic papers"

#: ../../skills.rst:12
msgid "**假设生成**: 从研究问题生成可测试的假设"
msgstr ""
"**Hypothesis Generation**: Generate testable hypotheses from research "
"questions"

#: ../../skills.rst:13
msgid "**实验设计**: 设计完整的实验配置"
msgstr "**Experiment Design**: Design complete experiment configurations"

#: ../../skills.rst:14
msgid "**论文撰写**: 通过 paper-orchestrator skill 套件（重写中）生成 Nature 风格学术论文 PDF"
msgstr ""
"**论文撰写**: Generate Nature style academic paper PDF through paper-"
"orchestrator skill suite (under rewriting)"

#: ../../skills.rst:15
msgid "**数据分析**: 分析实验数据并生成报告"
msgstr "**Data Analysis**: Analyze experiment data and generate reports"

#: ../../skills.rst:16
msgid "**智能体处理**: 智能体选择、生成和过滤"
msgstr "**Agent Processing**: Agent selection, generation, and filtering"

#: ../../skills.rst:19
msgid "Claude Code Skills"
msgstr "Claude Code Skills"

#: ../../skills.rst:21
msgid "研究工作流主要通过 Claude Code 的“skills-first”方式提供："
msgstr ""
"Research workflows are primarily provided through Claude Code’s “skills-"
"first” approach:"

#: ../../skills.rst:23
msgid "AgentSociety 内置研究 skills：随 VSCode 插件打包，可在插件树视图中浏览（只读）。"
msgstr ""
"AgentSociety built-in research skills: packaged with the VSCode plugin and "
"can be browsed in the plugin tree view (read-only)."

#: ../../skills.rst:24
msgid "Agent(Person) 扩展 skills：由后端 `/api/v1/agent-skills/*` 管理，支持扫描/导入/热重载。"
msgstr ""
"Agent (Person) extended skills: managed by the backend `/api/v1/agent-"
"skills/*`, supporting scanning/import/hot reload."

#: ../../skills.rst:26
msgid "**agentsociety-literature-search** - 文献检索"
msgstr "**agentsociety-literature-search** - Literature search"

#: ../../skills.rst:27
msgid "**agentsociety-hypothesis** - 假设管理（add, get, list, delete）"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-hypothesis** - Assumption management (add, get, list, delete)"

#: ../../skills.rst:28
msgid "**agentsociety-experiment-config** - 实验配置生成与验证"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-experiment-config** - Experimental configuration generation "
"and verification"

#: ../../skills.rst:29
msgid "**agentsociety-run-experiment** - 实验执行与监控"
msgstr "**agentsociety-run-experiment** - Experiment execution and monitoring"

#: ../../skills.rst:30
msgid "**agentsociety-analysis** - 数据分析与跨实验综合"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-analysis** - Data analysis and cross-experimental synthesis"

#: ../../skills.rst:31
msgid "**agentsociety-create-agent** - 自定义 Agent 生成与校验"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-create-agent** - Custom Agent generation and verification"

#: ../../skills.rst:32
msgid ""
"**agentsociety-paper-orchestrator** - Nature/Science 级论文生成（6-skill 状态机）"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-paper-orchestrator** - Nature/Science level paper generation "
"(6-skill state machine)"

#: ../../skills.rst:35
msgid "create-agent 技能"
msgstr "create-agent skills"

#: ../../skills.rst:37
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-create-agent`` 用于创建或修订工作区里的自定义 Agent 类型。它不是 PersonAgent "
"内置认知技能，而是研究工作流中的开发辅助 skill：当实验需要一个当前不存在的 Agent class 时，通常由 ``agentsociety-"
"experiment-config`` 分支调用。"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-create-agent`` Used to create or revise custom Agent types in"
" the workspace. It is not a built-in cognitive skill of PersonAgent, but a "
"development auxiliary skill in the research workflow: when the experiment "
"requires an Agent class that does not currently exist, it is usually called "
"by the ``agentsociety-experiment-config`` branch."

#: ../../skills.rst:39
msgid "**文件位置与扫描规则**:"
msgstr "**文件位置与扫描规则**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:41
msgid ""
"新 Agent 模块应放在 ``custom/agents/`` 下，例如 "
"``custom/agents/research/lab_agent.py``。"
msgstr ""
"New Agent modules should be placed under ``custom/agents/``, for example "
"``custom/agents/research/lab_agent.py``."

#: ../../skills.rst:42
msgid "扫描器会读取该目录下的 ``*.py``，但跳过路径片段包含 ``examples/`` 的文件。"
msgstr ""
"The scanner reads ``*.py`` in this directory, but skips files whose path "
"fragment contains ``examples/``."

#: ../../skills.rst:43
msgid "推荐一个文件一个主要 Agent class；一个文件中存在多个 ``AgentBase`` 子类时，扫描器也能发现。"
msgstr ""
"It is recommended to have one main Agent class per file; when there are "
"multiple ``AgentBase`` subclasses in a file, the scanner can also find it."

#: ../../skills.rst:45
msgid "**基类选择**:"
msgstr "**基类选择**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:51
msgid "基类"
msgstr "base class"

#: ../../skills.rst:52
msgid "适用场景"
msgstr "Applicable scenarios"

#: ../../skills.rst:53
msgid "``AgentBase``"
msgstr "``AgentBase``"

#: ../../skills.rst:54
msgid "简单实验、博弈/基准场景，开发者自行管理状态。"
msgstr ""
"Simple experiments, games/benchmark scenarios, developers manage the status "
"by themselves."

#: ../../skills.rst:55
msgid "``PersonAgent``"
msgstr "``PersonAgent``"

#: ../../skills.rst:56
msgid "需要 skills-first 工具循环、workspace、checkpoint/WAL 与持久化记忆。"
msgstr ""
"Requires skills-first tool loops, workspace, checkpoint/WAL and persistent "
"memory."

#: ../../skills.rst:58
msgid "**本地校验**:"
msgstr "**本地校验**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:67
msgid ""
"校验器会检查：目标文件为 Python 文件、至少有一个直接继承 ``AgentBase`` 或 ``PersonAgent`` 的类、``ask`` "
"/ ``step`` / ``dump`` / ``load`` 均为 ``async def``、模块可动态导入、目标类不是 abstract "
"class。创建完成后，在 VS Code 扩展中执行 **Scan Custom Modules** 让后端重新发现模块。"
msgstr ""
"The validator will check: the target file is a Python file, there is at "
"least one class that directly inherits ``AgentBase`` or ``PersonAgent``, "
"``ask`` / ``step`` / ``dump`` / ``load`` are all ``async def``, the module "
"can be imported dynamically, and the target class is not abstract class. "
"After creation, execute **Scan Custom Modules** in the VS Code extension to "
"let the backend rediscover the module."

#: ../../skills.rst:71
msgid "实验工作流"
msgstr "Experiment workflow"

#: ../../skills.rst:73
msgid "研究 pipeline 的主干是："
msgstr "The backbone of the research pipeline is:"

#: ../../skills.rst:75
msgid ""
"``literature-search → hypothesis → experiment-config → run-experiment → "
"analysis → paper-orchestrator``"
msgstr ""
"``literature-search → hypothesis → experiment-config → run-experiment → "
"analysis → paper-orchestrator``"

#: ../../skills.rst:77
msgid "实验相关的两个核心 skill 是："
msgstr "The two core skills related to experiments are:"

#: ../../skills.rst:83
msgid "Skill"
msgstr "Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:84
msgid "主要输入"
msgstr "main input"

#: ../../skills.rst:85
msgid "主要输出"
msgstr "main output"

#: ../../skills.rst:86
msgid "``agentsociety-experiment-config``"
msgstr "``agentsociety-experiment-config``"

#: ../../skills.rst:87
msgid "``SIM_SETTINGS.json``、已有 Agent/Env/Dataset 信息"
msgstr "``SIM_SETTINGS.json``, existing Agent/Env/Dataset information"

#: ../../skills.rst:88
msgid "``init_config.json``、``steps.yaml``、``config_params.py``"
msgstr "``init_config.json``、``steps.yaml``、``config_params.py``"

#: ../../skills.rst:89
msgid "``agentsociety-run-experiment``"
msgstr "``agentsociety-run-experiment``"

#: ../../skills.rst:90
msgid "``init_config.json`` + ``steps.yaml``"
msgstr "``init_config.json`` + ``steps.yaml``"

#: ../../skills.rst:91
msgid "``run/sqlite.db``、日志、artifacts、``pid.json``"
msgstr "``run/sqlite.db``, logs, artifacts, ``pid.json``"

#: ../../skills.rst:93 ../../skills.rst:107
msgid "推荐流程："
msgstr "Recommended process:"

#: ../../skills.rst:95
msgid "使用 ``research-pipeline where-am-i --json`` 确认当前阶段。"
msgstr ""
"Use ``research-pipeline where-am-i --json`` to confirm the current phase."

#: ../../skills.rst:96
msgid ""
"在 ``experiment-config`` 阶段先扫描模块；如果缺少 Agent 或 Env，再分支到 ``create-agent`` 或 "
"``create-env-module``。"
msgstr ""
"In the ``experiment-config`` stage, scan the module first; if Agent or Env "
"is missing, branch to ``create-agent`` or ``create-env-module``."

#: ../../skills.rst:97
msgid "运行 ``experiment-config check`` 或等价校验，确认配置和步骤文件可用。"
msgstr ""
"Run ``experiment-config check`` or equivalent verification to confirm that "
"the configuration and step files are available."

#: ../../skills.rst:98
msgid "启动实验时使用 ``run-experiment``；后台执行必须指定日志文件，避免丢失 verbose 输出。"
msgstr ""
"Use ``run-experiment`` when starting the experiment; a log file must be "
"specified for background execution to avoid losing verbose output."

#: ../../skills.rst:99
msgid "实验完成后检查 ``run/sqlite.db``、日志与 artifacts，再进入分析阶段。"
msgstr ""
"After the experiment is completed, check ``run/sqlite.db``, logs, and "
"artifacts before entering the analysis phase."

#: ../../skills.rst:103
msgid "分析工作流"
msgstr "Analysis workflow"

#: ../../skills.rst:105
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-analysis`` 面向已完成实验的数据解释、图表和报告生成。它要求目标 run 目录中已经存在 "
"``sqlite.db``；如果数据库不存在，应回到 ``run-experiment`` 或配置修复阶段。"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-analysis`` Data interpretation, graphs and report generation "
"for completed experiments. It requires that ``sqlite.db`` already exists in "
"the target run directory; if the database does not exist, you should fall "
"back to ``run-experiment`` or the configuration repair phase."

#: ../../skills.rst:109
msgid "**加载上下文**：读取 hypothesis、experiment config、steps 和 run 元数据。"
msgstr ""
"**加载上下文**: Read hypothesis, experiment config, steps and run metadata."

#: ../../skills.rst:110
msgid "**确认问题**：明确本次分析是验证假设、解释异常、比较组间差异，还是生成报告。"
msgstr ""
"**确认问题**: Clarify whether this analysis is to test hypotheses, explain "
"anomalies, compare differences between groups, or generate a report."

#: ../../skills.rst:111
msgid "**探索数据**：列出 SQLite 表，查看 schema、行数、关键字段和缺失情况。"
msgstr ""
"**探索数据**: List the SQLite table and view the schema, number of rows, key "
"fields and missing conditions."

#: ../../skills.rst:112
msgid "**提出发现**：先给出可检验发现，再决定需要哪些图表。"
msgstr ""
"**提出发现**: Give testable findings first, then decide which graphs are needed."

#: ../../skills.rst:113
msgid "**生成图表**：单实验默认最多 5 张图；每张图在报告中必须有一句说明。"
msgstr ""
"**生成图表**: A single experiment can have up to 5 pictures by default; each "
"picture must have an explanation in the report."

#: ../../skills.rst:114
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**写报告**：单实验输出到 ``presentation/hypothesis_{id}/``，跨实验综合输出到 ``synthesis/``。"
msgstr ""
"**写报告**: Single experiment output to ``presentation/hypothesis_{id}/``, "
"cross-experiment comprehensive output to ``synthesis/``."

#: ../../skills.rst:116
msgid "常用命令："
msgstr "Commonly used commands:"

#: ../../skills.rst:127
msgid "文献检索服务"
msgstr "Literature search service"

#: ../../skills.rst:129
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-literature-search`` 通过统一的远程检索服务收集学术文献，并把结果保存到工作区 ``papers/`` "
"目录。默认检索所有已配置数据源：``local``、``arxiv``、``crossref``、``openalex``。"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-literature-search`` Collect academic literature through a "
"unified remote search service and save the results to the workspace "
"``papers/`` directory. All configured data sources are retrieved by default:"
" ``local``, ``arxiv``, ``crossref``, ``openalex``."

#: ../../skills.rst:131
#, fuzzy
msgid "配置项："
msgstr "Configuration"

#: ../../skills.rst:138
msgid "搜索命令示例："
msgstr "Search command example:"

#: ../../skills.rst:145
msgid "输出约定："
msgstr "Output convention:"

#: ../../skills.rst:147
msgid ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` 是稳定索引，记录标题、作者、年份、来源、query、分数和本地 "
"``file_path``。"
msgstr ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` is a stable index, recording title, author,"
" year, source, query, score and local ``file_path``."

#: ../../skills.rst:148
msgid ""
"每篇文献保存为 ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``，这是后续 hypothesis、analysis 和 paper "
"技能引用的主要本地笔记。"
msgstr ""
"Each document is saved as ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``, which is the "
"main local note cited in subsequent hypothesis, analysis and paper skills."

#: ../../skills.rst:149
msgid ""
"原文 PDF 如需下载，应放在 ``papers/full_texts/``，并记录到 "
"``extra_fields.full_text.file_path``；不要把索引中的 ``file_path`` 从 Markdown 笔记替换成 "
"PDF。"
msgstr ""
"If the original PDF is to be downloaded, it should be placed in "
"``papers/full_texts/`` and recorded in ``extra_fields.full_text.file_path``;"
" do not replace ``file_path`` in the index from Markdown notes to PDF."

#: ../../skills.rst:150
msgid ""
"文献检索不会自动绕过出版商权限。PDF 下载只处理开放获取或用户授权的文件；没有开放 PDF 时，可以用 web research 补充 "
"Markdown 笔记并记录来源。"
msgstr ""
"Literature searches do not automatically bypass publisher permissions. PDF "
"downloads only process open access or user-authorized files; when there is "
"no open PDF, you can use web research to supplement Markdown notes and "
"record the source."

#: ../../skills.rst:153
msgid "Python API"
msgstr "Python API"

#: ../../skills.rst:155
msgid "研究技能也可以通过 Python API 直接调用。"
msgstr "Research skills can also be called directly through the Python API."

#: ../../skills.rst:158
msgid "文献技能 (literature)"
msgstr "Literature Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:160
msgid ""
"文献技能默认使用已经配置好的 ``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_URL`` 和 ``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_KEY``"
" 调用统一检索服务。推荐优先使用 ``search_literature_and_save``，而不是直接调用底层 "
"``search_literature``： 前者会把检索结果落到工作区中，确保后续 Agent、Claude Code 和论文写作技能 "
"都能通过本地文件继续引用这些文献。"
msgstr ""
"By default, the literature skill uses the configured "
"``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_URL`` and ``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_KEY`` to call the "
"unified search service. It is recommended to use "
"``search_literature_and_save`` instead of calling the underlying "
"``search_literature`` directly: the former will drop the search results into"
" the workspace, ensuring that subsequent Agent, Claude Code and paper "
"writing skills can continue to reference these documents through local "
"files."

#: ../../skills.rst:191
msgid "**保存结果**:"
msgstr "**保存结果**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:193
msgid ""
"每篇检索结果都会保存为 ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``。 这个 Markdown "
"文件是稳定的本地文献笔记，包含标题、检索词、年份、期刊、 DOI/URL、摘要、作者和相关内容片段。"
msgstr ""
"Each search result will be saved as ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``. This "
"Markdown file is a stable local literature note that contains title, search "
"terms, year, journal, DOI/URL, abstract, author, and related content "
"fragments."

#: ../../skills.rst:196
msgid ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` 会同步更新。索引中的 ``file_path`` 指向本地 Markdown "
"文献笔记，因此插件中的 ``@引用`` 可以复制为 ``@papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``，供 Claude Code 或"
" Agent 读取。"
msgstr ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` will be updated simultaneously. "
"``file_path`` in the index points to the local Markdown document note, so "
"``@引用`` in the plug-in can be copied to ``@papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md`` "
"for Claude Code or Agent to read."

#: ../../skills.rst:199
msgid "重复运行检索时会生成新的本地文献笔记，并追加到索引中，便于保留不同检索轮次的上下文。"
msgstr ""
"When a search is run repeatedly, new local literature notes are generated "
"and appended to the index, allowing context to be retained across different "
"search rounds."

#: ../../skills.rst:201
msgid "**原文下载（由 Claude/Agent 按需执行）**:"
msgstr "**原文下载（由 Claude/Agent 按需执行）**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:203
msgid ""
"文献技能不会在 Python API 中硬编码下载策略。检索结果会尽量保留 "
"``doi``、``url``、``pdf_url``、``full_text_url``、``download_url``、 "
"``open_access``、``best_oa_location`` 等元信息；Claude Code 或 Agent "
"可以基于这些线索按需下载开放获取原文。"
msgstr ""
"Documentation skills do not hardcode download policies in the Python API. "
"The search results will try to retain meta-information such as ``doi``, "
"``url``, ``pdf_url``, ``full_text_url``, ``download_url``, ``open_access``, "
"``best_oa_location``; Claude Code or Agent can download the open access "
"original text on demand based on these clues."

#: ../../skills.rst:208
msgid "建议的下载约定："
msgstr "Recommended download conventions:"

#: ../../skills.rst:210
msgid "原文 PDF 放在 ``papers/full_texts/*.pdf``。"
msgstr "The original PDF is located at ``papers/full_texts/*.pdf``."

#: ../../skills.rst:211
msgid ""
"优先使用 API 返回的 PDF 直链；arXiv 论文可从 ``/abs/<id>`` 转为 "
"``https://arxiv.org/pdf/<id>.pdf``。"
msgstr ""
"Priority is given to PDF direct links returned by the API; arXiv papers can "
"be converted from ``/abs/<id>`` to ``https://arxiv.org/pdf/<id>.pdf``."

#: ../../skills.rst:213
msgid "DOI 仅作为落地页线索，不保证能直接得到 PDF；如果需要下载，应确认最终响应确实是 PDF。"
msgstr ""
"The DOI is only used as a landing page clue, and there is no guarantee that "
"the PDF will be obtained directly; if you need to download it, you should "
"confirm that the final response is indeed a PDF."

#: ../../skills.rst:214
msgid "下载完成后，可在对应索引条目的 ``extra_fields[\"full_text\"]`` 中记录:"
msgstr ""
"After the download is completed, it can be recorded in "
"``extra_fields[\"full_text\"]`` of the corresponding index entry:"

#: ../../skills.rst:224
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"如果没有找到开放原文，也可以记录 ``{\"status\": \"no_candidate\"}`` 或 ``{\"status\": "
"\"failed\", \"reason\": \"...\"}``，便于插件页面显示状态。"
msgstr ""
"If the open original text is not found, you can also record ``{\"status\": "
"\"no_candidate\"}`` or ``{\"status\": \"failed\", \"reason\": \"...\"}`` to "
"facilitate the plug-in page to display the status."

#: ../../skills.rst:229
msgid ""
"许多 CrossRef/OpenAlex 结果只提供 DOI 或落地页，不一定有开放 PDF。 Claude/Agent 不应绕过出版商权限，也不应把 "
"HTML 落地页当作 PDF 保存。"
msgstr ""
"Many CrossRef/OpenAlex results only offer a DOI or landing page, not "
"necessarily an open PDF. Claude/Agent should not bypass publisher "
"permissions or save HTML landing pages as PDFs."

#: ../../skills.rst:232
msgid ""
"**数据源**: - ``local``: RAGFlow 本地知识库 - ``arxiv``: arXiv 预印本平台 - ``crossref``:"
" CrossRef DOI 元数据库 - ``openalex``: OpenAlex 学术图谱 (2.5亿+ 论文)"
msgstr ""
"**数据源**: - ``local``: RAGFlow local knowledge base - ``arxiv``: arXiv "
"preprint platform - ``crossref``: Crossref DOI metadata repository - "
"``openalex``: OpenAlex scholarly graph (250 million+ papers)"

#: ../../skills.rst:238
msgid "**配置**: 需要在 ``.env`` 文件中配置 API:"
msgstr "**配置**: API needs to be configured in ``.env`` file:"

#: ../../skills.rst:247
msgid "假设技能 (hypothesis)"
msgstr "Hypothesis Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:263
msgid "实验技能 (experiment)"
msgstr "Experiment Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:284
msgid "分析技能 (analysis)"
msgstr "Analysis Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:302
msgid ""
"跨实验对比不再使用独立综合 skill，而是作为 ``agentsociety-analysis`` 的 Stage 5 在 Claude Code "
"中完成。"
msgstr ""
"The cross-experiment comparison no longer uses independent comprehensive "
"skills, but is completed in Claude Code as Stage 5 of ``agentsociety-"
"analysis``."

#: ../../skills.rst:306
msgid "论文技能 (paper)"
msgstr "Paper Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:308
msgid ""
"论文生成由 6 个 plugin skill 组成的状态机驱动，通过 ``paper-orchestrator`` 作为唯一入口点调度。Python 包"
" ``agentsociety2.skills.paper`` 提供非 LLM 逻辑（状态管理、适配器、 LaTeX 编译）。"
msgstr ""
"The paper generates a state machine driver composed of 6 plugin skills, and "
"schedules it through ``paper-orchestrator`` as the only entry point. Python "
"package ``agentsociety2.skills.paper`` provides non-LLM logic (state "
"management, adapters, LaTeX compilation)."

